li.p: Collections are an accessible way to manage your icons library, and the core of our web app. Do you want to know how to use them? Press the right arrow or use the top navigation to watch the guide.
Browse the packs or search icons and add them to your active collection with this button.
This is a list of your collections. You can change their names, and they are sorted by use. Click on one of them to start using it.
Click on this button to create a new collection.
This is your active collection. A collection can have up to 256 icons if you are a registered user or 50 if you are not registered.
Access this menu to edit your collection; edit your icons separately, duplicate your collection, sort the icons in your collection or share it with the rest of the world.
Drag & drop your SVGs to the active collection to upload your own icons. There is a limitation of 3 icons per collection for free users.
Not enough space? Now you can see your collections in fullscreen mode to make it easier for you.
Are you done with this collection? Delete it and create a new one here.
And that is all. If you have any questions, you can contact our support team here.
Thank you for using Flaticon, we hope you enjoy our service
